main event: A formation of three unidentified flying objects was observed over Ft Meade, Maryland during the early hours of September 1-3, 1953.
interesting points: The objects were observed for about 10 minutes., The source of the report was military., There was no physical evidence or photographs present., The investigation concluded it could not be determined what the objects were., The location of observation at Ft Meade, Md., is significant due to its military background.
